    M_PER_SEC = URIRef("http://qudt.org/vocab/unit/M-PER-SEC")  # Metre per second is an SI derived unit of both speed (scalar) and velocity (vector quantity which specifies both magnitude and a specific direction), defined by distance in metres divided by time in seconds. The official SI symbolic abbreviation is mu00b7s-1, or equivalently either m/s.
